                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.7353b/105: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Great Britain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harvey</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-08-03T13:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 3, 1922—1 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received August 3—12:25 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>333. My 301, July 18, 6 p.m. Mr. Frederick Kerr who represents Western Union
                    Telegraph Co. at Lisbon informs me he knows that Foreign Office instructed
                    British Minister at Lisbon to inform Portuguese Government it would be greatly
                    to its disadvantage if it granted Azores permits. He believes Portuguese
                    Government would welcome strong pressure from American Government to justify it
                    in disregarding British pressure.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Harvey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
